    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1891-05-04T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1891-05-04T00:00:00-05:00" n="118" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d118">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Egan</persName> to Mr.
                                <persName type="to">Blaine</persName>
                    </hi>.</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Legation of
                                    the United States</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Santiago</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1891-05-04">
                            <hi rend="italic">May 4,
                            1891</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Mr. Egan informs Mr. Blaine that the good offices of the United States,
                        Brazil, and France have been most cordially accepted by the Government of
                        Chile and the revolutionists, those of England and Germany having been
                        declined.</p>
            </div>
